    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Don't Forget Catalogs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Yale School of Music piano curator William Harold letter on Michelle Slatella's August 24 article notes piano tuners and teachers usually have catalogs containing piano lamps</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Michelle Slatalla's article about shopping for unusual items on the Web was great (''Site Invites Shoppers to Wax Eloquent,'' Online Shopper, Aug. 24), but if she is still looking for a piano lamp, she could phone her piano tuner or teacher and save a lot of time. We tuners usually have quite a few piano supply catalogs, and most of them have a broad range of piano lamps. Not everything you are looking for is on the Web yet.</p>
        <p>WILLIAM HAROLD  Fairfield, Conn.</p>
        <p>The writer is the piano curator at the Yale School of Music.</p>
      </block>
